text: Carryover from last week: the billing migration is still blocked on the vendor sandbox, which is the headline item for today.

section: Discussion

sub: Billing Migration

text: Sara walked through the migration plan. The new provider sandbox was provisioned late, so end-to-end testing slipped by roughly four days. We agreed the slip is recoverable inside the Q3 window if testing starts this week.

risk: Vendor sandbox availability | severity: high | mitigation: dual-track with the legacy gateway until parity is proven
blocker: Provider sandbox credentials not yet issued | owner: Marco Ricci | since: 2026-06-19

quote: We do not flip the production switch until we have a clean dry run on real invoice data. | by: Sara Okonkwo

decision: Run the migration behind a feature flag and dark-launch to 5% of accounts first | by: Layla Hassan | at: 2026-06-23

sub: Launch Scope

text: Marco proposed cutting the in-app analytics dashboard from the Q3 launch to protect the date. After discussion the room agreed analytics ships in Q4 as a fast-follow.

decision: Defer the analytics dashboard to Q4; Q3 launch covers billing + SSO only | by: Marco Ricci | at: 2026-06-23

sub: Budget Check

text: We confirmed the migration cost against the approved infrastructure line.

